Pre-Game Insights: Cyprus and Latvia have met only twice in history.
Cyprus are coming off a terrible Euro 2024 qualifying campaign, losing all eight matches.
Latvia lost all but one game in their own Euro qualifying campaign last year.
Head coach Temur Ketsbaia has called up 25 players for this month's double-header against Latvia and Serbia.
Miscellaneous Highlights: This is a clash of two lowly-ranked teams lacking in serious quality.
Cyprus might capitalize on their home advantage in this match and prevail narrowly.
Others: The match will take place at the AEK Arena in Larnaca on Thursday.
Latvia have lost their last three international games, failing to score in all three and conceding eight times.
After going nine games without a win, Cyprus beat Lithuania 1-0 in a friendly game back in November.
Cyprus are ranked 125th in the world, whereas Latvia are in 136th position in the FIFA World Rankings.
Head coach Paolo Nicolato has announced a 26-man squad for this month's double-header against Cyprus and Liechtenstein.
